sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sp_rel_widget_clone"><sp_rel_widget_clone action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><child display_value="Owner_complince_data_table">28c937d61b597010b85ee3fb234bcb0e</child><cloned>2021-07-14 20:47:56</cloned><last_validated>2021-07-14 20:47:56</last_validated><parent display_value="Data Table from URL Definition">8ae61f55cb21020000f8d856634c9c93</parent><payload><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><sp_widget><category>standard</category><client_script><![CDATA[function($scope, $rootScope, $location, spUtil, $timeout, spAriaFocusManager) {
	var canNavigate = true;
	if ($scope.data.dataTableWidget)
		angular.extend($scope.data.dataTableWidget.options, $scope.options);

	$scope.$on('data_table.click', callDataClick);

	$scope.$on('select2.ready', function(e, $el){
		if ($scope.data.invalid_table){
			e.stopPropagation();
			$el.select2('open');
		}
	})

	$scope.selectedTable = {
		displayValue: $scope.data.table,
		value: $scope.data.table
	}

	function resetParams(){
		delete $scope.data.p;
		delete $scope.data.o;
		delete $scope.data.d;
		delete $scope.data.q;
		delete $scope.data.table;
	}

	$scope.onChange = function() {
		resetParams();
		$scope.data.table = $scope.selectedTable.value;
		$scope.data.fields = "";  // reset
		$scope.data.invalid_table = false;
		getData(true);
	}
	
	function callDataClick(e, parms) {											
			var oid = $location.search().id;
			var p = $scope.data.page_id || 'form';
			var s = {id: p, table: parms.table, sys_id: parms.sys_id, view: $scope.data.view};
			if (oid == p) {
				s.spa = 1;
				var t = $location.search();
				s = angular.extend(t, s);
				$rootScope.$broadcast('$sp.list.click', s);
			}

			var newURL = $location.search(s);
			spAriaFocusManager.navigateToLink(newURL.url());										
	}

	function getData(updateUrl) {
		var f = $scope.data;
		spUtil.update($scope).then(function(data) {
				$scope.data.dataTableWidget = null;
				$timeout(function(){
					$scope.data.dataTableWidget = data.dataTableWidget;
					angular.extend($scope.data.dataTableWidget.options, $scope.options);
					if (updateUrl)
						setPermalink(f.table);
				});
		});
	}

	function setPermalink(table) {
		$scope.ignoreLocationChange = true;
		var searchParms = $location.search();
		var search = {
			spa: 1,
			table: table,
			id: searchParms.id
		};
		$location.search(search);
	}
}]]></client_script><controller_as/><css>.widget-data-table .clearfix {
  display: none;
}

.panel-primary .panel-heading {
  button:not(.btn-default) {
    &amp;:focus {
      outline-color: #FFFFFF;

      box-shadow: 0px 0px 5px #FFFFFF;
    }
  }
}
</css><data_table>sp_instance_table</data_table><demo_data/><description/><docs/><field_list>title,glyph,color,sp_page</field_list><has_preview>false</has_preview><id>data-table-from-url</id><internal>false</internal><link/><name>Data Table from URL Definition</name><option_schema>[{"hint":"Show Instance option title instead of the table's plural label","name":"use_instance_title","default_value":"false","section":"Presentation","label":"Use Instance Title","type":"boolean"},{"hint":"If enabled, show the filter in the breadcrumb section of the table","name":"enable_filter","default_value":"false","section":"Presentation","label":"Enable Filter","type":"boolean"}]</option_schema><public>false</public><roles>snc_external,snc_internal</roles><script><![CDATA[(function() {
	deleteOptions(['table','field_list','filter','order_by', 'order_direction','order','maximum_entries']);
	if (input) {
		data.table = input.table;
		data.view = input.view;
	} else {
		data.table = $sp.getParameter('table') || $sp.getParameter('t');
		data.view = $sp.getParameter('view');
	}

	if (!data.table) {
		data.invalid_table = true;
		data.table_label = "";
		return;
	}

	var gr = new GlideRecordSecure(data.table);
	if (!gr.isValid()) {
		data.invalid_table = true;
		data.table_label = data.table;
		return;
	}

	// page is where the record URLs go, URL parameter wins
	data.page_id = $sp.getParameter("target_page_id");
	if (!data.page_id) {
		var sp_page = $sp.getValue('sp_page');
		if (sp_page) {
			var pageGR = new GlideRecord('sp_page');
			pageGR.get(sp_page);
			data.page_id = pageGR.id.getDisplayValue();
		}
	}

	// widget parameters
	data.table_label = gr.getLabel();
	data.fields = $sp.getListColumns(data.table, data.view);
	copyParameters(data, ['p', 'o', 'd', 'filter']);
	copyParameters(data, ['relationship_id', 'apply_to', 'apply_to_sys_id']);
	data.filterACLs = true;
	data.show_new = true;
	data.show_keywords  = true;
	data.show_breadcrumbs = true;
	data.fromUrl = true;
	data.headerTitle = (options.use_instance_title == "true") ? options.title : gr.getPlural();
	data.enable_filter = input.enable_filter || options.enable_filter == true || options.enable_filter == "true";
	data.dataTableWidget = $sp.getWidget('widget-data-table', data);
	

	function copyParameters(to, names) {
		names.forEach(function(name) {
			data[name] = $sp.getParameter(name);
		})
	}

	// in case this widget is tied to the wrong instance type
	function deleteOptions(names) {
		names.forEach(function(name) {
			delete options[name];
		})
	}
})()]]></script><servicenow>true</servicenow><sys_class_name>sp_widget</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2015-07-28 19:54:45</sys_created_on><sys_id>8ae61f55cb21020000f8d856634c9c93</sys_id><sys_mod_count>415</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Data Table from URL Definition</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Service Portal - Core" source="com.glide.service-portal">17b9cc34db142010543b9647db961926</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sp_widget_8ae61f55cb21020000f8d856634c9c93</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-12-11 06:26:31</sys_updated_on><template><![CDATA[<div>
  <div ng-if="data.invalid_table">
    <div class="alert alert-info">
      <span ng-if="data.table_label">${Table not defined} '{{data.table_label}}'</span>
      <span ng-if="!data.table_label">${Select table on field below or specify on URL} ?id=list&amp;table=table_name</span>
    </div>
    <sn-record-picker field="selectedTable" table="'sys_db_object'"
                      display-field="'label'"
                      value-field="'name'"
                      display-fields="'name'"
                      search-fields="'label,name'" page-size="100" on-change="onChange()" ></sn-record-picker>
  </div>
  <div ng-if="data.dataTableWidget && !data.invalid_table">
  	<sp-widget widget="data.dataTableWidget"></sp-widget>
  </div>
</div>]]></template></sp_widget></payload><sys_class_name>sp_rel_widget_clone</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>vijay.maddula</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-07-14 20:47:56</sys_created_on><sys_id>e0c937d61b597010b85ee3fb234bcb13</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>28c937d61b597010b85ee3fb234bcb0e</sys_name><sys_package display_value=" Housing Compliance" source="x_colac_housing_co">fceca5371bf764908f6f54e4604bcb60</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value=" Housing Compliance">fceca5371bf764908f6f54e4604bcb60</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sp_rel_widget_clone_e0c937d61b597010b85ee3fb234bcb13</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>vijay.maddula</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2021-07-14 20:47:56</sys_updated_on></sp_rel_widget_clone></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sp_widget"><sp_widget action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><category>custom</category><client_script><![CDATA[function($scope, $uibModal,  nowAttachmentHandler, spAttachmentUpload, $rootScope, spUtil, snAttachmentHandler, spModal, $log, spAriaUtil,$document) {
  /* widget controller */
  var c = this;
	/* Validate form before submission */
	c.validateForm=function(){
		if($('#mainForm')[0].checkValidity()){
			c.addRecord();
		}
	}
	
	
	
	//adding custom code from here: Vijay
	//ATTACHMENT FUNTIONALITY
	//Comment by vijay
		//$scope.data.table = "x_cask_renters_ass_assistance_submissions";
//	$scope.data.table = "x_colac_housing_co_responses";
	//$scope.data.sys_id = c.data.sys_id;

	$scope.errorMessages = [];
	$scope.attachmentHandler = new nowAttachmentHandler(setAttachments, appendError);
	$scope.data.action = "";
  //$scope.parseInt = parseInt; //use in household member visibility //Vijay Comment
	
	spUtil.recordWatch($scope, "sys_attachment", "table_sys_id=" + $scope.data.sys_id, function(response, data) {
		$scope.attachmentHandler.getAttachmentList();
		if (response.data) {
			var options = {};
			options.operation = response.data.operation;
			options.filename = response.data.display_value;
			options.sys_id = $scope.data.sys_id;
			options.table = $scope.data.table; 
			options.state = (response.data.record && response.data.record.state) ? response.data.record.state.value : "";
			//broadcast only if operation is update...we don't need insert and other record updates for now
			if (options.operation === "update" && options.state === "not_available")
				$rootScope.$broadcast("attachment.updated",options);

			////c.server.update(); 

			//c.data.attachments = response.data.attachments;
			
			
			
		}
	});

	$scope.$evalAsync(function() {
		$scope.attachmentHandler.setParams($scope.data.table, $scope.data.sys_id, 1024 * 1024 * $scope.data.maxAttachmentSize);
		$scope.attachmentHandler.getAttachmentList();
	});

	$scope.hasAttachments = function() {
		return $scope.attachments && $scope.attachments.length != 0;
	};

	$scope.canWrite = function() {
		return $scope.data.canWrite;
	};
	
	$scope.dropFiles = function(files) {
		if (!$scope.data.canDragAndDrop) {
			spUtil.addInfoMessage(data.noDragDropMsg);
			return;
		}
		spAttachmentUpload.uploadAttachments($scope.attachmentHandler, files);
	};
	
	
	

	$scope.confirmDeleteAttachment = function(attachment) {
		var appendTo = $scope.data.appendToId ? $document.find('#'+$scope.data.appendToId) : null;
		spModal.confirm("${Delete Attachment?}",  appendTo).then(function() {
			$scope.attachmentHandler.deleteAttachment(attachment);
			$scope.setFocusToAttachmentButton();
		});
	};


	$scope.$on('dialog.upload_too_large.show', function(e){
		$log.error($scope.data.largeAttachmentMsg);
		spUtil.addErrorMessage($scope.data.largeAttachmentMsg);
	});

	$scope.$on('added_attachment', function(evt) {
		$scope.data.action = "added";
		spUtil.update($scope);
	});

	$scope.$on('sn.attachment.scanned', function(evt) {
		$scope.attachmentHandler.getAttachmentList("list");
	});

	$scope.$on('sp.record.can_write', function(evt, answer) {
		$scope.data.canWrite = answer;
	});

	function appendError(error) {
		$scope.errorMessages.push(error);
		spUtil.addErrorMessage(error.msg + error.fileName);
	}

	function setAttachments(attachments, action) {
		if ($scope.submitting == true)
			return;

		$scope.attachments = attachments;
		if (!action)
			return;

		if (action === "added") {
			spAriaUtil.sendLiveMessage($scope.data.attachmentSuccessMsg);
		}

		$scope.data.action = action;
	spUtil.update($scope);
	}
	
	//custom code ends here: Vijay
	
	/* function to add submission as record to table*/
	c.addRecord=function(){
		// c.data.var_name = $scope.c.data.var_name
		c.data.owner_name = $scope.c.data.owner_name;
		c.data.proj_name = $scope.c.data.proj_name;
		c.data.owner_address = $scope.c.data.owner_address;
		c.data.contact_person = $scope.c.data.contact_person;
		c.data.proj_address = $scope.c.data.proj_address;
		c.data.contract_amt = $scope.c.data.contract_amt;
		c.data.phone_num = $scope.c.data.phone_num;
		c.data.rcs = $scope.c.data.rcs;
		c.data.fax_num = $scope.c.data.fax_num;
		c.data.email_address = $scope.c.data.email_address;
		/* signature section */
		c.data.owner_signature = $scope.c.data.owner_signature;
		c.data.owner_name_sign = $scope.c.data.owner_name_sign;
		c.data.owner_date = $scope.c.data.owner_date;
		c.data.pwcu_by = $scope.c.data.pwcu_by;
		c.data.pwcu_date = $scope.c.data.pwcu_date;
		
		/* Certification Regarding Transactions */
		c.data.transactions_auth_sign = $scope.c.data.transactions_auth_sign;
		c.data.transactions_auth_sign_name_title = $scope.c.data.transactions_auth_sign_name_title;
		c.data.transactions_project_name = $scope.c.data.transactions_project_name;
		c.data.transactions_date = $scope.c.data.transactions_date;
		
		/* Compliance Survey*/
		c.data.mbe = $scope.c.data.mbe;
		c.data.wbe = $scope.c.data.wbe;
		c.data.na = $scope.c.data.na;
		// Ethnicity
		c.data.eth_wa = $scope.c.data.eth_wa;
		c.data.eth_ba = $scope.c.data.eth_ba;
		c.data.eth_na = $scope.c.data.eth_na;
		c.data.eth_ha = $scope.c.data.eth_ha;
		c.data.eth_api = $scope.c.data.eth_api;
		c.data.eth_hj = $scope.c.data.eth_hj;
		
		/* Wage Compliance Guidelines */
		c.data.pwcgg_auth_sign = $scope.c.data.pwcgg_auth_sign;
		c.data.pwcgg_company_name = $scope.c.data.pwcgg_company_name;
		c.data.pwcgg_auth_sign_name_title = $scope.c.data.pwcgg_auth_sign_name_title;
		c.data.pwcgg_date = $scope.c.data.pwcgg_date;
		
		c.data.action = "addRecord"
		/* Completion message */
		c.server.update().then(function(response){
			c.data={};
			alert("Thank You for completing this form!");
		})	
		
  }
	
	/* function to deselect mbe/wbe when na chosen */
	c.be_na=function(){
		if($scope.checked_na == true){
			$scope.checked_mbe=false;
			$scope.checked_wbe=false;
		}
	}
	
	/* function to deselect mbe/wbe when na chosen */
	c.be_mbe_wbe=function(){
		if($scope.checked_mbe == true || $scope.checked_wbe == true){
			$scope.checked_na=false;
		}
	}
	
	
	/* function to display MBE/WBE certification upload
	c.displayUpload = function (id_of_checkbox) {
		console.log(c);
		// Get the checkbox
		var checkBox = $document[0].getElementByID(id_of_checkbox);
		// Get upload button and label
		var id_of_upload = id_of_checkbox + "_certification";
		var upload = $document[0].getElementByID(id_of_upload);
		var label = upload.previousElementSibling;

		// If the checkbox is checked, display the output text
		if (checkBox.checked == true){
			upload.style.display = "block";
			label.style.display = "block";
		} else {
			upload.style.display = "none";
			label.style.display = "none";
		}
	}*/
}

]]></client_script><controller_as>c</controller_as><css>.two-column {

<!-- Nondiscrimination/Affirmative Action -->
<fieldset>
<legend class="text-center"><h3>
	<center><b>NONDISCRIMINATION EQUAL EMPLOYMENT PRACTICES/AFFIRMATIVE ACTION POLICY<br>CONSTRUCTION CONTRACTORS</b></center>
</h3></legend>
<p>Los Angeles Administrative Code (LAAC), Division 10, Chapter 1, Article 1, Section 10.8 requires entities doing business with the City to comply with a Nondiscrimination/Affirmative Action Program. (Refer questions regarding these requirements to the HCIDLA Prevailing Wage  Compliance Unit, at (213) 808-8909). In order to comply, it is necessary that the bidder/proposer/respondent complete, sign and return with the bid/proposal/response, the following:</p>
<ol type="A">
    <b><li>For all contracts, the contractor agrees to adhere to the following Nondiscrimination Clause:</li></b>
    <ol>
        <li>The contractor agrees and obligates the company not to discriminate during the performance of this contract against any employee or applicant for employment because of the employee's or applicant's race, religion, national origin, ancestry, sex, age, sexual orientation, disability, marital status, domestic partner status, or medical condition; and</li>
        <li>All subcontracts awarded under this contract shall contain a like Nondiscrimination Clause.</li>
    </ol><font size="-1"><br/></font>
    <b><li>For construction contracts from $1,000 to under $5,000 the contractor agrees to:</li></b>
    <ol>
        <li>Adhere to the Nondiscrimination Clause above;</li>
        <li>Designate a management level Equal Employment Opportunity Officer; and</li>
        <li>Adhere to Equal Employment Practices provisions as outlined in LAAC §10.8.3.</li><font size="-1"><br/></font>
    </ol>
    <b><li>For construction contracts of $5,000 or more the contractor agrees to:</li></b>
    <ol>
        <li>Adhere to the Nondiscrimination Clause above;</li>
        <li>Designate a management level Equal Employment Opportunity Officer as provided for in Section "E" below;</li>
        <li>Adhere to Equal Employment Practices provisions as outlined in LAAC §10.8.3;</li>
        <li>Complete the Ethnic Composition of Total Work Force Report; and</li>
        <li>Sign and submit an Affirmative Action Plan. The bidder must submit one of the two following plans:</li>
        <ol type="a">
            <li><u>Plan A. Los Angeles City Affirmative Action Plan</u> ("Los Angeles City Affirmative Action Requirements") which is an approved plan requiring only signature of acceptance along with the Ethnic Composition of Work Force and submittal to be effective; or</li>
            <li><u>Plan B. The Bidder's own Affirmative Action Plan for approval</u>, which must contain at a minimum all of the elements of the City's Plan.</li><font size="-1"><br/></font>
        </ol>
    </ol>
    <b><li>Subcontractors:</li></b>
    <ol>
        <li>The contractor shall require the same documents indicated above to be submitted <u>for subcontractors</u> of any contract awarded by the City; and</li>
        <li>The contractor shall be responsible for obtaining the Affirmative Action Plans from its subcontractors. Additional forms are available from the HCIDLA Prevailing Wage Compliance Unit.</li>
    </ol>
</ol>
</fieldset>
  
<!-- Wage Compliance Guidelines -->
<fieldset>
<legend class="text-center"><h3>
  <center><b><u>LOS ANGELES HOUSING + COMMUNITY INVESTMENT DEPARTMENT<br><font size="+1">PREVAILING WAGE COMPLIANCE UNIT</font></u><br><br>PREVAILING WAGE COMPLIANCE GENERAL GUIDELINES</b></center>
</h3></legend>

<ol>
    <li>The owner and general contractor must complete and submit <i>Compliance Packages</i> for approval to the Prevailing Wage Compliance Unit as a condition to commence construction. Please address packages to:<br/><br/>
<p><center>
Attn: Prevailing Wage Compliance Unit<br/>
Los Angeles Housing + Community Investment Department<br/>
1200 W. 7<sup>th</sup> Street, 8<sup>th</sup> Floor<br/>
Los Angeles, CA 90017<br/><br/>
</center></p>
    </li>
    <li>Once packages are approved, a Pre-Construction Conference will be held to inform the developer and general contractor of all compliance regulations.</li>
    <li>An <i>Authorization to Issue a Notice to Proceed</i> (ANTP) will be issued to the developer after the successful completion of the Pre-Construction Conference.</li>
    <li>The general contractor and all subcontractors are required to adhere to applicable Federal and/or State Prevailing Wage requirements. If both wage requirements apply, the higher of the two will be enforced.</li>
    <li>A contractor's signatory must be listed on the contractor's State Contractor's License; if he/she is not listed on the license, the contractor must obtain a notarized letter authorizing that individual to sign in representation.</li>
    <li>If a contractor has multiple Payroll Officers or if he/she appoints a new Payroll Officer during the course of construction, a Certification of Understanding and Authorization must be submitted for each Payroll Officer.</li>
    <li>Please be advised that contractors are required to utilize Employee Sign-in Sheets on the job site, and may be required to submit these upon request to HCIDLA.</li>
    <li>The general contractor and all subcontractors must submit weekly Certified Payrolls no more than 2 weeks after the end of each work week. In addition, Employee Information Sheets must be submitted for all employees along with the first payroll they are on. Please update information for all employees that obtain a change of address or work classification.</li>
    <li>The general contractor and all subcontractors must submit a Section 3 Report form with their final payroll at the completion of their work on the project.</li>
    <li>Material(s) Supplier's invoices must be submitted for all billings for 'Materials' on the List of Subcontractors form included in each disbursement request.</li>
    <li>The project will be monitored by the HCIDLA Prevailing Wage Compliance Unit under the authority of the Bureau of Contract Administration's Office of Contract Compliance.</li>
    <li>Every new subcontractor must have their Compliance Package approved prior to beginning work, and must follow all guidelines followed by the general contractor, including submitting weekly payrolls.</li>
    <li>If the developer wishes contest the application of a compliance fine, the developer may submit a written appeal with an explanation and corresponding evidence to support their position.</li>
    <li>HCIDLA does not engage in direct correspondence with subcontractors. Please do not refer subcontractors to HCIDLA as they will be immediately referred to the project developer and/or their contracting party.</li>
    <li>To obtain a wage decision from HCIDLA, your project must be within 90 days of the start of construction date (with a HCIDLA issued ANTP); otherwise, per Federal law, any said wage decision would be immediately voided and a new one must be obtained at a later date.</li>
    <li>On the List of Subcontractors form, if 'Labor' is checked, certified payrolls will be required for the billing period; if 'Materials' is checked, invoices for the billing period will be required.</li>
    <li>It is prohibited to use Federal Funds for Lobbying - Byrd Anti-Lobbying Amendment (Section 319 of Public Law 101-121)</li>
    <li>Access and Retention of Records (24 CFR 92.508): The HOME recipient, the State of California, the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development, the Comptroller General of the United States, or any of their duly authorized representatives, shall have access to any books, documents, papers, and records of the contractor which are directly pertinent to this specific contract, for the purpose of making audit, examination, excerpts, and transcriptions. Under State HOME regulations all required records must be maintained by the contractor for five years after grantee makes final payments and all other pending matters are closed (this is two years longer than the federal requirement of three years).</li>
    <li>HCIDLA requires all Certified Payrolls to be submitted through LCP Tracker. HCIDLA will activate this account for the General Contractors. General Contractors are required to complete the Prime Approver training course provided by LCP Tracker. Please contact Christina Nagel, Project manager at LCP Tracker, for more information at 714-669-0052 x107 and <a href="http://www.lcptracker.com">http://www.lcptracker.com</a> to get started.</li>
    <li>Projects that receive Federal funding may use apprentices and they are subject to the United States Department of Labor's Office of Apprenticeship. For projects that receive Federal funding and/or receive State funding and/or are public works, mandatory Federal Apprenticeship is required in addition to State Apprentice requirements.<br/><br/>
<center><b><u>FOR STATE FUNDED and/or PUBLIC WORKS PROJECTS</u></b></center><br/>
</li>
    <li>The General State Prevailing Wage Rate is applicable to all projects. The State Residential Prevailing Wage Rate may be applicable on residential projects (defined as 4 stories or less). Note: On residential projects, The General State Prevailing Wage Rate must be paid to workers with job classifications not found on the State Residential Prevailing Wage Rate determination.</li>
    <li>If applying for a State Residential Prevailing Wage Rate determination the owner cannot sign the contract with its general contractor before obtaining the wage determination and it cannot put the job out to bid for 45 days from the issuance of the request to the State DIR.</li>
    <li>All contractors on state funded and/or public works projects are subject to State Apprenticeship Requirements as per the Division of Apprenticeship Standards.</li>
    <li>Please print the Owner Compliance Package and all documents required in the Package, sign, scan the entire package, and electronically send such to HCIDLA. Through your signature below you agree to hold the original Owner Compliance Package and all documents required in the Package until requested by HCIDLA. Owner shall provide the completed original Owner Compliance Package and all documents required in the Package to HCIDLA located at 1200 W. 7<sup>th</sup> St. 8<sup>th</sup> Floor, Los Angeles, CA 90017 within five days of request.</li>
    <li>If the Owner compliance package is electronically submitted, owner agrees that the signatures scanned into .pdf sent by email to HCIDLA shall be deemed original signatures.</li>
</ol>
  
  <p>
    By entering my name in below, I attest that I am the owner and that the information in this application is accurate.
  </p>
	<!-- Text input -->

<script>
  /* Function creates a help button to all labels with "help-text" class.
     Requires there to be an element with "help-blocks" class as a sibling to
     appropriately populate title */
  function addHelpButton(){
    let labels = document.querySelectorAll(".help-text");
    
    for(let i = 0; i < labels.length; ++i){
      let btn = document.createElement("button");
      btn.innerHTML = "i";
      btn.type = "button";
			btn.classList.add("btn");
			btn.classList.add("btn-secondary");
      
      btn.setAttribute("data-toggle", "tooltip");
      btn.setAttribute("data-placement", "top");
      
      let siblings = labels[i].parentNode.childNodes;
      let help_text = '';
      console.log(siblings);	
      for(let sibling of siblings.values()){
          console.log(sibling);
        if(sibling.classList == "help-blocks"){
          console.log('in');
          help_text = sibling.innerHTML;
        }
      }
      btn.setAttribute("title", help_text);
      
      labels[i].after(btn);
    }
  }
  //addHelpButton();
</script>]]></template></sp_widget></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sys_script_8b2d96e91b85f8508f6f54e4604bcb5f
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>true</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>true</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>x_colac_housing_co_responses</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition table="x_colac_housing_co_responses">u_statusCHANGESTOapp_process^EQ<item display_value="Application in process" endquery="false" field="u_status" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="CHANGESTO" or="false" value="app_process"/><item endquery="true" field="" goto="false" newquery="false" operator="=" or="false" value=""/></filter_condition><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Create OCP owner users</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/ ) {

    // Generate password
	//e_mail_address

    createLLViaEmail();

    function createLLViaEmail() {
        try {
            //gs.addInfoMessage("test1");
            var newpw = "";
            var availablechars = "1234567890";
            for (var x = 0; x < 4; x++) {
                var randomNumber = Math.floor(Math.random() * availablechars.length);
                newpw += availablechars[randomNumber];
            }

            if (current.email_owner !== "") {
                var num_str = current.number;
                var num = num_str.match(/\d+/);
                var number = parseInt(num);

                var user_id = current. email_owner+ "_" + number;
                var nameArr = current.owner_name;

                /* var name = nameArr.split(" ");
                var first_name = name[0].toString();
                var last_name = name[1].toString(); */

                var name = nameArr.split(' ');
                var first_name = name[0];
                var last_name = nameArr.substring(name[0].length).trim();

                /* if(last_name == "" ){
                	user_id = first_name + "_" + number;
                } else {
                	user_id = first_name  + "." + last_name + "_" + number;
                } */


                var gr_user = new GlideRecord('sys_user');
                gr_user.addQuery("email", current.email_owner);
                gr_user.query();
                if (!gr_user.next()) {
                    gr_user.initialize();
                    gr_user.user_name = user_id;
                    gr_user.first_name = current.first_name;
                    gr_user.last_name = current.owner_last;
                    gr_user.email = current.email_owner;
                    gr_user.x_colac_housing_co_compliance_package_type = 'owner';
                    //gr_user.department = '45a0a478db791cd00d4af12aaf9619f6';
                    gr_user.password_needs_reset = true;
                    gr_user.user_password.setDisplayValue(newpw);
                    gr_user.insert();
					
					// below code replced in User table

//                     var user_role = new GlideRecord('sys_user_has_role');
//                     user_role.initialize();
//                     user_role.user = gr_user.sys_id + "";
//                     user_role.role = 'f7f6f2371bfb64908f6f54e4604bcbdc'; // Assigning x_colac_housing_co.responses_user role
//                     user_role.insert();


                    // Add snc_external role to user upon creation
                    var user_role_inherit = new GlideRecord('sys_user_has_role');
                    user_role_inherit.initialize();
                    user_role_inherit.user = gr_user.sys_id;
                    user_role_inherit.inherited = false;
                    user_role_inherit.role = '940ba702933002009c8579b4f47ffbe2'; // Assigning snc_external role
                    user_role_inherit.insert();

                    current.owner = gr_user.sys_id;
                    current.response_user = gr_user.sys_id;
                    current.update();


                    gs.addInfoMessage('Username: ' + user_id + ' Your temporary password is  -' + " " + newpw);
                    gs.eventQueue('x_colac_housing_co.OCP_registration', current, user_id, newpw);
                } else {
                    current.response_user = gr_user.sys_id;
                    current.update();

                    gs.eventQueue("x_colac_housing_co.user.already.present", current, current.email_owner);
                    //gs.eventQueue("x_colac_housing_co.user.already.present",current,current.u_owner.contactemail);
                }
            } else {
                gs.addErrorMessage('To create Landlord record with Email only, Landlord Name and Email are required.');
            }
        } catch (e) {
            gs.error("CASK: Create landlord users BR: " + e);
        }

    }
})(current, previous);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>naveed.mohammed</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2021-06-29 20:07:17</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>8b2d96e91b85f8508f6f54e4604bcb5f</sys_id><sys_mod_count>61</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Create OCP owner users</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value=" Housing Compliance" source="x_colac_housing_co">fceca5371bf764908f6f54e4604bcb60</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value=" Housing Compliance">fceca5371bf764908f6f54e4604bcb60</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_8b2d96e91b85f8508f6f54e4604bcb5f</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>vijay.maddula</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2021-09-30 19:32:08</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=8b2d96e91b85f8508f6f54e4604bcb5f"/></record_update>
